The two dashes I encountered in the days I regularely published my papers in Poland were the hyphen, used as a hyphen and en dash, so in both combined words and number ranges, and a longer dash, used as an em dash would be.

I love the Oxford comma in English. I actually tried to introduce it into Polish, but it always got edited out of any of my scholarly papers. Polish has a strict rule of never using a comma before "i", which is our equivalent of "and". I do use the Oxford comma in the study materials I prepare for my students at uni though. They don't mind it.

